Replaced the single long scrolling page with anchor links with the
same left-sidebar-click / right-pane-content pattern already used
on the Blueprint and Brownfield detail pages — click a section in
the left nav, only that section's content shows on the right.

- components/doc/DocClient.tsx: new client component holding all
  9 sections (Overview, Sign in & accounts, Dashboard, Greenfield,
  Brownfield, Knowledge Base, Plans & features, Settings & account,
  FAQ) as a tab-switched view, same content as before.
- app/doc/page.tsx: reduced to a thin server wrapper that just
  renders DocClient and keeps the page metadata.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (23/23 pages,
/doc still present in route table), no lint errors on either file.
